notes: Scorers: JA Howard (Australia) and CJ Reece (South Africa)
Umpire SJ Davis was originally selected to stand in this match. Due to an ear infection DJ Harper stood in the middle while Davis acted as TV umpire.
12th Men: A Symonds (Australia) and M Hayward (South Africa)
Australia were fined 2 overs for a slow over rate
Gary Kirsten kept wicket for the 47th over (conceding 8 runs, no byes), whilst Hall bowled

stories.title: Waugh "astonished" at over reduction
stories.summary:
Australian captain Steve Waugh was very disappointed at his team's loss in
the final match of the Super Challenge 2000 series against South Africa but
said that he was "astonished" at the two over deduction made to his team's
allocated overs as it

stories.title: Proteas come from the clouds to level indoor series
stories.summary: South Africa has tied the inaugural Super Challenge 2000 series at Melbourne's Colonial Stadium at one match apiece with a eight run win in the third and final match of what has proved to be a very innovative and enjoyable series
